Mamelodi Sundowns celebrates with fans during the CAF Champions League 2021/22 match between Mamelodi Sundowns and Al Ahly SC on the 12 March 2022 at, FNB Stadium, Soweto / Pic Sydney Mahlangu/BackpagePix JOHANNESBURG - Pitso Mosimane and Al Ahly were keen to get a measure of revenge when they visited Mamelodi Sundowns in the Caf Champions League. Sundowns took their Caf Champions League group A clash to the FNB Stadium. A small percentage of fans watched Peter Shalulile score the decisive goal. It ended 1-0Â  to the Brazilians, afterward Mosimane acknowledged the Sundowns fans. They responded by giving their former coach warm applause. It's a significant moment because there had been more ugly scenes before the game. The Al Ahly bus is said to have been disrupted by some local fans on its way to the stadium. On the field, Downs now top group A with 10 points and look good to advance to the knockouts.